{{Infobox football club | clubname = Liria | image = | image_size = 200px | fullname = Klubi i Futbollit Liria | nickname = {{nowrap|{{lang|sq|Arpagjik't}}}} | founded = {{Start date and years ago|1930|df=y}} | ground = [[Përparim Thaçi Stadium]] | chrtitle = President | chairman = Ilijaz Ilijazi | mgrtitle = Coach | manager = Ante Vujanović | league = [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]] | season = [[2017–18 Football Superleague of Kosovo|2017–18]] | position = Football Superleague of Kosovo, 5th | website = http://www.liriafc.com/ | pattern_la1 = _black_stripes | pattern_b1 = _blackstripes | pattern_ra1 = _black_stripes | pattern_sh1 = | pattern_so1 = | leftarm1 = FFFFFF | body1 = FFFFFF | rightarm1 = FFFFFF | shorts1 = 000000 | socks1 = 000000 | pattern_la2 = _goldstripes | pattern_b2 = _amber_stripes | pattern_ra2 = _goldstripes | pattern_sh2 = | pattern_so2 = | leftarm2 = dc143c | body2 = dc143c | rightarm2 = dc143c | shorts2 = dc143c | socks2 = dc143c }} '''KF Liria''' ({{lang-sq|Klubi Futbollistik Liria}}), commonly known as '''Liria''' is a professional [[Football team|football club]] based in [[Prizren]], [[Kosovo]]. The club play in the [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]], which is the top tier of football in the country.
==History== KF Liria is one of the oldest football clubs in Kosovo. They played in the Yugoslav lower leagues until the beginning of [[World War II]], when the region was annexed by [[Albania]]. Liria, then renamed as '''Prizreni''', participated for one season in the [[1942 Albanian Superliga]]. After winning the [[1942 Albanian Superliga#North Zone|North Zone]], they qualified to the final stage of the tournament, where they lost in the [[1942 Albanian Superliga#Semifinals|semifinals]] against [[KF Tirana|Tirana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sktirana.com/public/kuvend/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=466|title=Historia e Kampionatëve të Shqipërise. Vol. III: Vitet 1939–42|language=Albanian|publisher= [[SK Tirana]]|date= 2004}}</ref>
After the end of the World War II, the club returned to the [[Yugoslav football league system]], having played on a series of occasions in the [[Yugoslav Second League]]. After the [[Kosovo War]], Liria began competing in the [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]], the top tier of football in the [[Kosovo]].
KF Liria were the winners of the 2006–07 [[Kosovar Cup]], beating [[KF Flamurtari|Flamurtari]] 3–0 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]] in the final held at [[Pristina City Stadium]].
KF Liria were the winners of the 2009–10 Kosovar Cup, beating [[KF Vëllaznimi|Vëllaznimi]] 3–1 in [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] in Pristina City Stadium. Liria is the only club in Kosovo that have supporters almost in all the territory of the Kosovo, practically Liria is most supported club in Kosovo together with [[FC Prishtina|Prishtina]].
