'''Stade Akid Lotfi''' ({{Lang-ar|ملعب العقيد لطفي}}) is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Tlemcen]], [[Algeria]].  It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[WA Tlemcen]].  The stadium holds 18,000 people.

==Algeria national football team matches==

The Stade Akid Lotfi has hosted four games of the [[Algeria national football team]], against [[Qatar]] in 1989, [[Burundi]] in 1992, [[Ghana]] in 1993, and the [[Ivory Coast]] in 1993.

